              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The mean values of the fast flux and the epithermal",
                "flux per unit In E, as measured from the standard",
                "reaction 27Al(n,p)27Mg and the reaction 68Zn(n,g)69mZn",
                "which waas used as internal standard, were 1.7x10**12",
                "and 8.4 x 10**10 n/cm2/s, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 67 cm3 ORTEC HPGe intrinsic-N coaxial detector",
                "with a resolution of 2.0 keV FWHM and 12.3 % relative",
                "efficiency. Data collection was performed in 4096",
                "channels with a Ortec DSPec digital gamma-ray",
                "spectrometer.Initial sets of measurements by high",
                "resolution gamma-ray spectrometry of about 5 min",
                "duration were performed, with 1-15 min decay; then,",
                "after decay times of between 1 to 2 h, the samples were",
                "measured for 1 -3h."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Zinc foils with masses of about 70 mg and aiuminum",
                "standards were irradiated for times between 3 and",
                "20 min, under cadmium cover, using the pneumatic tube",
                "facility of the reactor."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Total error. The systematic uncertainty",
                "contribution to all cross-section measurements are:",
                "* 2.8% corresponding to! the uncertainty of the",
                "       reference cross-section value,",
                "* 2% to 3% to the absolute efficiency (depending on the",
                "  energy and counting geometry),",
                "* 1% to sample purity, and",
                "* 1% to other contributions (sample and monitor",
                "  concentrations, nickel isotopic abundance, decay",
                "  constants, self-attenuation correction), amounting",
                "  to a total systematic uncertainty of 4.3% to 4.8%."
              ]
            }
          ],
